<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="LT4" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        f(x) = \begin{cases}
                        \frac{11}{3} \, x^{2} + b - x, &amp; x \leq 2 \\
                        -3 \, x + 9, &amp; x &gt; 2
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=2</m> for 
the function <m>h(x)</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        h(x) = \begin{cases}
                        5 \, x - 16, &amp; x &lt; 2 \\
                        -2, &amp; x = 2 \\
                        3 \, x - 12, &amp; x &gt; 2 \\
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>, let <m>b=-\frac{29}{3}</m>.</li>
                <li>
The function <m>h(x)</m> has a
removable discontinuity.
                </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
